class Solution(object):
    def findMissingAndRepeatedValues(self, grid):
        """
        :type grid: List[List[int]]
        :rtype: List[int]
        """
        n = len(grid)
        total = sum(range(1, n*n + 1))
        flat_grid = [item for sublist in grid for item in sublist]
        sum_grid = sum(flat_grid)
        diff = total - sum_grid
        seen = set()
        dup = -1
        for num in flat_grid:
            if num in seen:
                dup = num
                break
            seen.add(num)
        missing = dup + diff
        return [dup, missing]
